[Pyramid]
A pyramid is a single-base polyhedron whose lateral faces are all triangles
that touch at a common vertex.

[Regular Pyramid]
A pyramid whose base is a regular polygon.

[Surface Area of a Pyramid]
Since pyramids only have one base, the base's surface area is only accounted
for once: S = L + B.

[Lateral Area of a Pyramid]
The lateral area L of a pyramid is equal to 1/2lp, where l is the slant height
of the pyramid and lp is the perimeter of the base.

[Slant Height]
The height of one of the triangular lateral faces of a regular pyramid.

