If all of the measures of the regular square pyramid shown in the figure above
are multiplied by 1/4, what is the surface area of the pyramid?

Perimeter...........
p = 4 * (16 / 4)
p = 4 * 4
p = 16

Slant length........
l = 10 / 4
l = 2.5

Lateral area........
L = 1/2lp
L = 1/2(2.5)(16)
L = 20

Base area...........
B = (16 / 4)^2
B = 4^2
B = 16

Total surface area..
S = L + B
S = 20 + 16
S = 36

